    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
    <p>The Sony WH-1000XM5 and the Sennheiser Momentum 4 Wireless are two of the best premium wireless headphones you can buy in 2026, and they represent two different visions of what a flagship over-ear headphone should be. Sony's WH-1000XM5 is the fifth generation of the line that effectively defined the modern noise-canceling headphone category, and it doubles down on adaptive noise cancellation, call quality, and smart features. Sennheiser's Momentum 4 Wireless leans into the company's audiophile heritage, prioritizing sound quality, battery life, and a refined, music-first experience.</p>

    <p>The two headphones share a lot on paper — both are over-ear designs with active noise cancellation, Bluetooth multipoint, custom companion apps, and USB-C charging — but they feel distinctly different in use. The Sony is the more technologically ambitious product, with eight microphones, two processors, and an adaptive sound control system that adjusts settings based on your location and activity. The Sennheiser is the more traditional audio product, with a focus on a cleaner sound signature, class-leading 60-hour battery life, and a more understated design language.</p>

    <p>Choosing between them comes down to what you value most: the Sony wins on noise cancellation, call quality, and smart features, while the Sennheiser wins on sound quality, battery life, and price. After spending months with both headphones across commutes, flights, calls, and focused listening sessions, here is the detailed comparison to help you choose.</p>

